Turkey summons U.S. diplomat over espionage report
Turkey's Foreign Ministry summoned the country's highest-ranking U.S. diplomat for clarification on a report on U.S. and British espionage in Turkey.
Deputy Prime Minister Bülent said the U.S. chargé d'affaires and Turkish officials discussed the report on Monday.
German magazine Der Spiegel and online magazine The Intercept reported that documents provided by former U.S. National Security Agency analyst Edward Snowden show that Turkey has been a priority intelligence target for U.S. and British intelligence services.
