The largest Chinese companies have united against Alibaba
Chinese companies, including China's largest commercial real estate developer Dalian Wanda Group and Internet giants Tencent Holdings (social networks, messenger, etc.) and Baidu (the largest Chinese search engine), are creating a company that will compete in the online trading market with Alibaba.
However, catching up with the miracle of the Chinese Internet, which left behind even its American rivals - eBay and Amazon.com, will not be easy.
Union of the Largest
The companies plan to invest 5 billion yuan ($ 814 million) in the joint venture, 70% of it will be owned by Wanda and 15% by each of the Internet companies, the Wanda Group said in a statement.
It is planned to register a company in Hong Kong.
The joint venture will combine Baidu's search services with the popular social platform WeChat (the largest social network in China, the number of users of which is about 438 million people), Tencent and Wanda infrastructure.
In addition to a network of 40 luxury hotels, the Wanda Group manages at least 49 commercial properties throughout China and 40 shopping centers.
Last year, the company invested 50 billion yuan (more than $8 billion) to build a film studio and theme park in Qingdao, a city in eastern China on the shores of the Yellow Sea.
The project is expected to attract more than 1 million visitors annually and generate a profit of $960 million.
In addition, Wanda owns the American cinema chain AMC Entertainment Holdings, which makes the company the largest cinema operator in the world.
By 2015, Wanda plans to equip all its shopping centers, hotels and entertainment venues with e-commerce services, the development of which will be engaged in the created competitor Alibaba.
According to Dong Ce, who will lead the new company, thanks to the merger, Wanda will be able to increase the number of users of its e-commerce services from the current 40 million people to 100 million by next year.
The new platform should become the world's largest online-to-offline platform, Dong Ce notes.
The essence of online-to-offline (O2O) commerce is to attract buyers on the Internet so that they come to ordinary offline stores or buy other traditional services.
A classic example of O2O is coupon services like Groupon or Vigoda.ru.
"O2O is the biggest 'pie' in online commerce," said Wanda ceo Wang Jianlin (quoted by Bloomberg).
"Now there is no real O2O site in China, and in this situation the chances are approximately equal for everyone," he said.
China's e-commerce market is the largest in the world, and McKinsey & Co. estimates that its volume will more than triple by 2015 compared to 2011, to $395 billion.
The number of Chinese Internet users has grown to 632 million, Bloomberg cites official statistics: this is more than the population of any country in the world, with the exception of India.
And according to forecasts, by 2015 this number could grow to 850 million people.
Union of the Richest
Tencent CEO Ma Huateng until recently was China's richest man, however, according to bloomberg's millionaire index, Alibaba founder Jack Ma has already overtaken him by $ 5.5 billion.
Jack Ma's fortune is estimated at $ 21.8 billion, of which $ 11 billion falls on his share in Alibaba.
Baidu CEO Robin Li now ranks third among China's richest people, while Wanda's Wang Jianlin is fourth in the rankings.
"This battle is very interesting to watch: the three richest people are joining forces to challenge the even richer," Cao Lei, director of the Chinese Center for E-Commerce Research in Hangzhou, told Bloomberg.
But he believes that the new company is unlikely to be able to seriously compete with Alibaba immediately after creation: "Rome cannot be built in one day."
The fact that it is not so easy to compete with Alibaba not only for new companies, but also for the honored leaders of world e-commerce, is evidenced by the report on the financial performance of Alibaba for the last quarter published yesterday.
Alibaba is often described as a cross between eBay and Amazon.com, but from April to June, the Chinese company earned more than both of its American competitors combined.
Alibaba's net profit for the period is almost twice as high as that of competitors - it grew almost three times year-on-year and amounted to $ 1.99 billion.
"Alibaba still has huge potential to generate money, thanks in large part to its mobile apps," an analyst at Hong Kong's Arete Research Service told Bloomberg.
According to the updated Alibaba prospectus on the website of the US Securities and Exchange Commission, the number of active mobile users of the company's services in July amounted to 188 million, which significantly exceeds the March figure (163 million people).
At the same time, 32.8% of all Alibaba transactions over the past quarter accounted for mobile devices.
Alibaba will have to name the value of its shares before the IPO.
According to the average estimate of 11 analysts surveyed by Bloomberg, the company could be valued at $187 billion after selling the shares.
According to Bloomberg sources, Alibaba's debut on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) may take place as early as September 16.
The company's road-show, preceding this event, starts on September 3.
It is expected that Alibaba's IPO will be a record in the history of the NYSE and will allow the company to raise about $ 20 billion.
Until now, the record for the volume of funds raised on US exchanges belonged to the Visa payment system, which in 2008 conducted an initial public offering of its shares, earning $ 17.9 billion.
At least half of the food products in retail chains should be of Russian production, according to State Duma deputies.
They have drafted a bill on the subject.
We are talking about amendments to Art. 8 of the Federal Law "On the Basics of State Regulation of Trade Activities in the Russian Federation" and to the Tax Code.
The purpose of the document is to introduce protective measures against Russian food producers.
An important clarification, according to the bill, at least 50 percent of domestically produced products in stores should be for each type of product.
