But just a couple of minutes later, shells and bullets whistled from all sides.
"Judging by the information I was given, we had a corridor, we were allowed to go out," says the acting deputy commander of the battalion, who has the call sign "Lermontov".
And when we descended between Polypolya and Chervonoselsky into the lowlands, crossfire began from anti-tank guided missiles, from "zushki", 30-millimeter grenade launchers, automatic BMD guns, small arms.
There were four cars in front of me and three in the back, in the end there were only two cars left.
An officer with the call sign "Lermontov" says: almost immediately at least 60 people were killed, dozens were injured, many died later.
The surviving militants are now receiving medical care from those they came to kill.
Now the prisoners are surprised that the so-called "terrorists" treat them well, give them food and medicine.
While their own commanders actually deceived them and doomed them to certain death.
We were betrayed simply," they say.
A column, the whole battalion, to be destroyed.
Like many of his comrades, Oleksiy joined the Donbass battalion as a volunteer, because the Ukrainian news told about the atrocities allegedly committed by "separatists" in the southeast.
Already here Alexey saw a completely different picture.
His mother was killed in Luhansk – and not just anyone, but the Ukrainian military.
A friend called me, told me that there was mortar shelling, that most likely it was the Ukrainian armed forces," says one of the soldiers, Oleksiy.
I then wanted to leave the battalion.
We were not allowed out of Ilovaisk, they said that we were in the ring.
I have already agreed with the commander, the report has already been written about leaving.
We were immediately taken from the training camp from Zurakhovo to Ilovaysk.
According to the prisoners, 300-350 people were stuck in the "cauldron" near Ilovaisk.
Now some survivors admit that if it were possible to turn back the clock, they would never join the punitive battalion.
The militia handed over all the prisoners to the DPR security forces.
Everyone will be tested for involvement in war crimes.
