Twitter tried to become more interesting for new users
The microblogging service Twitter has changed the process of registering users in order to quickly involve new participants in active interaction with the platform.
This measure should reduce the number of people who abandoned their microblogs.
Now new Twitter users will view a large number of accounts recommended by the service during registration in order to immediately make their reading circle.
Recommendations are made on the basis of the interests indicated during registration.
In this case, Twitter automatically checks the subscription box for all automatically selected accounts.
Because of this, the user will have to personally remove the ticks so as not to read those who are not interesting to him.
If earlier users of the microblogging service saw only the avatars of recommended users, now Twitter displays a sample of one of the popular tweets of the blogger to help make an impression of a person.
This is the largest change to the Twitter registration page in the last three years.
Recently, Twitter has been actively working on modernizing the service.
Such activity is primarily due to the ongoing attempts of the service to achieve break-even.
In 2014, the microblogging service faced a slowdown in the growth of the user base and a drop in reader activity.
The company at the moment desperately needs more loyal consumers, who, having entered once, would remain for a long time.
This is the only way to ensure a stable flow of advertising funds.
